other_tests.procedure_name: Transabdominal hysterectomy with pelvic lymphatic dissection
other_tests.findings: Intraoperatively, the uterine body was enlarged and soft, cervix was enlarged about 5 cm in diameter, with a 6 cm x 5 cm cervical canal mass invading the plasma membrane layer with blood in the uterine cavity.

Postoperative pathology showed minimal deviation adenocarcinoma of the cervix (MDA), invading the lower uterine body, with intravascular embolism; cancer metastases were detected in 2/11 left pelvic lymph nodes, 2/9 right pelvic lymph nodes, and 2/2 common iliac lymph nodes.

CEA (+), P16 (−), Ki67-MIB1 (hot zone 30%), ER (−), P53 (−), PR (−), Vimentin (−), Bcl-2 (−), CK7 (+), Muc-6 (partial +), CK20 (−), CDX2 (−), Villin (−), Napsin-A (−), Muc-1 (+), Muc-2 (−), Muc-5AC (+).
